      <item>
        <title>Date format for template</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[motopascyyy]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p><a class="mention" href="https://forums.getdrafts.com/u/agiletortoise">@agiletortoise</a> will probably need to confirm, but the preview action on its own won’t “process” the templates. Processing the templates means scanning for any of the appropriate syntaxes (like [[date]]) and then converting them in the text (either in memory or in the actual draft).</p>
<p>This makes sense to me because you can’t always guarantee that text matching a typical template isn’t meant to actually just be the text. The preview action is basically a way of throwing the current draft into a Markdown (or other) parser and then converting that into HTML so that it looks pretty. It’s not a preview of what the template would look like now if you were to trigger an action. I hope this helps explain it a bit.</p>
          <p><a href="https://forums.getdrafts.com/t/date-format-for-template/11338/8">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
